olonise public debates on racism, social class, education and social policy.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aCritical race theory. 0aPost-racialismzGreat Britain. 0aRacismzGreat Britain. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Discrimination & Race Relations.2bisacsh1 aBhopal, Kalwant, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBristol UP/Policy Press Complete eBook-Package 2024z978311129965540uhttps://doi.org/10.56687/9781447360193?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781447360193423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781447360193/original  a978-3-11-129965-5  Bristol UP/Policy Press Complete eBook-Package 2024b2024  aGBV-deGruyter-alles